rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: Airspace
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: A defined three dimensional region of space relevant to air traffic.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: AirspaceActivation
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: Information about the operational status of the airspace.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: AirspaceGeometryComponent
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: The role of the component in the airspace geometry. If the geometry of an airspace is composed of single volume, then the attributes of this association class may be left empty.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: AirspaceVolume
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: A defined volume in the air, described as horizontal projection with vertical limits.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: AirspaceVolumeDependency
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: The relationship between the geometry of an AirspaceVolume and the geometry of another (parent) Airspace.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: GeoBorder
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: A physical or political border. In general, it will be the border between two countries or States but could also be a coastline, the description of the bank of an important river, or any other geographical shape which can be named and used to describe the border of an airspace. If two countries/States have more than one common border, each one will be an occurrence of this entity.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: Curve
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: A one-dimensional geometric primitive, representing the continuous image of a line.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: Point
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: A zero-dimensional object that specifies geometric location. One coordinate pair or triplet specifies the location.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: Surface
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: A 2-dimensional primitive and is composed of one or more surface patches as specified in ISO 19107:2003, 6.3.17.1. The surface patches are connected to one another.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: Navaid
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: A service providing guidance information or position data for the efficient and safe operation of aircraft supported by one or more radio navigation aids.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: EnRouteSegmentPoint
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: Indicates a point associated with a defined EnRoute segment.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: PointReference
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: Defines the location of a designated point using a combination of angles and distances based on the guidance service. The set of angles and distances must not under specify the location. The indications that are part of the PointReference must locate the same designated point.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: SegmentPoint
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: Indicates a point associated with a defined segment.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: TerminalSegmentPoint
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: Indicates a point or a condition associated with a defined segment leg.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: DesignatedPoint
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: A geographical location not marked by the site of a radio navigation aid, used in defining an ATS route, the flight path of an aircraft or for other navigation or ATS purposes.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: SignificantPoint
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: A link class that allows selecting between a navaid system, a runway point, an airport reference point, an aiming point or a fix designated point. SignificantPoint accounts for a specified geographical location used to define an ATS route, the flight path of an aircraft or for other navigation/ATS purposes.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: OrganisationAuthority
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: A group of people, businesses, administrative concerns, or other entities that are systematically structured and managed to meet a need or to pursue collective goals on a continuing basis. This group has the ability to delegate roles, responsibilities, and authority over cognizant areas. For example: ATS Organisations, Aircraft Operating Agencies, States, Groups of States, companies, government entities, etc.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: OrganisationAuthorityAssociation
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: A type of hierarchical or associative relationship between two organizations or authorities showing ownership, supervision or membership.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: Route
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: A specified route designed for channelling the flow of traffic as necessary for the provision of air traffic services, from the end of the take-off and initial climb phase to the commencement of the approach and landing phase.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: RoutePortion
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: A group of two or more consecutive segments of the same route, which have the usage and/or the same flight restrictions.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: RouteSegment
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: A portion of a route to be flown usually without an intermediate stop, as defined by two consecutive significant points.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: AirTrafficControlService
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: A kind of service that provides control and separation services to aircraft in the air.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: Service
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: The provision of tangible goods, information, instructions, guidance, etc. to pilots, flights, aircraft operators and other personnel and institutions concerned with flight operations.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: TrafficSeparationService
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: A kind of service that provides control and separation services, to aircraft in the air and on the ground.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: AircraftCharacteristic
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: Classification, properties, and equipment capabilities of aircraft, such as airplane, balloon, helicopter, etc.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: AirspaceLayer
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: The portion of airspace between two specified vertical levels.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: PropertiesWithSchedule
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: An abstract class that is used for associating a group of feature properties with a repetitive time period, occurring cyclically inside the validity of the Feature Timeslice, during which these properties have specific values.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: StandardLevelColumn
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: A column of consecutive cruising levels within a standard level table.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: ObstacleAssessmentArea
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: The geometry of surfaces used to define the altitude the length of a segment, holding pattern, etc., in function of the obstructions located in the area.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: NilReasonEnumeration
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: Indicates the reason for a null value.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: AerodromeReference
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: Aerodromes may be identified by: * their ICAO codes ("KDFW"), OR * (for unlisted aerodromes) their names ("Dallas Fort Worth") PLUS significant point * The aerodrome name can also include a 3 character IATA Alternate Identifier such as "DFW"

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: AtcUnitReference
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: Reference to an Air Traffic Control organization of any type: unit, sector, etc.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: ConstrainedAirspace
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: Constrained Airspace such as Flow Constrained Area (FCA)

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: Feature
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: The Feature type is the parent of all FIXM complex types that describe physical objects or events. It is used as a marker to messaging and other tools that the contained information is to be treated as an unit and not further decomposed. Feature carries information about the ultimate source of its contained data in the "Provenance" attribute group. Implicitly, this information qualifies all the contained elements, unless one of them overrides it locally. It is expected that applications will use this to record their own meta-data about the information contained in the feature.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: Direction
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: Represents a compass bearing as an angle in the range [0,360].

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: SignificantPoint
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: A location type restricted to lat/long location, fix (waypoint) location, or FRD (radial distance offset).

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: AirspeedChoice
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: The airspeed choice indicates that airspeed can either be expressed as specific with a speed condition or a speed range between lower and upper bounds.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: AirTrafficType
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: The type of flight value associated with the point. It is associated with the first point on the route and any subsequent point where the type of flight value changes.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: AltitudeChoice
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: The altitude choice allows to either represent a specific altitude or an altitude range with a lower and upper bound

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: Count
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: Represents positive integer counts of objects.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: FleetPriority
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: Used to assign relative priorities to things and events. A lower number means a higher priority.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: FlightRules
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: The regulation, or combination of regulations, that governs all aspects of operations under which the pilot plans to fly.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: FreeText
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: Provides a standard representation for elements that may contain any text, such as comments and notes.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: GroundspeedChoice
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: The groundspeed choice indicates that groundspeed can either be expressed as specific with a speed condition or a speed range between lower and upper bounds.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: IcaoAircraftIdentifier
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: ICAO standard nomenclature of aircraft manufacturer and type.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: LateralOfftrack
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: Represents a lateral offtrack which can either be an offset or weather deviation.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: VerticalRange
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: Represents a vertical range from a lower bound altitude to an upper bound altitude.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: Aircraft
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: This is a main aircraft class that contains all the information about the aircraft.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: AircraftAddress
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: .Aircraft Address: A code that enables the exchange of text-based messages between suitably equipped Air Traffic Service (ATS) ground systems and aircraft cockpit displays.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: AircraftCapabilities
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: Groups all the aircraft's capabilities.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: AircraftPerformanceCategory
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: .Aircraft Performance Category: A coded category assigned to the aircraft based on a speed directly proportional to its stall speed, which functions as a standardized basis for relating aircraft manoeuvrability to specific instrument approach procedures.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: AircraftRegistration
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: .Aircraft Registration Mark: A unique, alphanumeric string that identifies a civil aircraft and consists of the Aircraft Nationality or Common Mark and an additional alphanumeric string assigned by the state of registry or common mark registering authority.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: AircraftType
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: .Aircraft Type: The manufacturer and model of the airframe expressed either as an ICAO-approved designator or a text description.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: EngineType
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: .Engine Type: The category of the aircraft engine.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: StandardCapabilitiesIndicator
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: .Standard Capabilities Indicator: This element indicates the aircraft carries the set of capabilities considered standard by the appropriate authority.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: WakeTurbulenceCategory
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: .Wake Turbulence Category: ICAO classification of the aircraft wake turbulence, based on the maximum certified take off mass.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: CommunicationCapabilities
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: .Communications Capabilities: The serviceable communications equipment, available on the aircraft at the time of flight, and associated flight crew qualifications that may be used to communicate with ATS units.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: NavigationCapabilities
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: .Navigation Capabilities: The serviceable navigation equipment available on board the aircraft at the time of flight and for which the flight crew is qualified.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: SurveillanceCapabilities
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: .Surveillance Capabilities: The serviceable Secondary Surveillance Radar (SSR) and/or Automatic Dependent Surveillance (ADS) equipment available on the aircraft at the time of flight that may be used to identify and/or locate the aircraft.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: AssignedIndicator
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: .Ranked 4D Trajectory Assignment Status: An indication whether the Ranked 4D trajectory has been assigned by the Air Navigation Service Provider (ANSP).

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: RankedTrajectory
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: .Ranked 4D Route: This is the route associated with a single Ranked 4D trajectory for a flight. It indicates the intent of the flight and includes the path over the surface of the earth, the altitude and the speed for the flight. .Ranked 4D Trajectory: A series of desired 4D trajectories, with tolerances supplied if necessary by the airspace user to define when the next ranked trajectory should be used.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: MeteorologicalData
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: .Meteorological Data: In a predicted trajectory, the instantaneous temperature and wind vector used at the 4D Point for creating the 4D trajectory.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: Point4D
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: .4D Point: Identifies the location, altitude and time of a trajectory point.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: PointRange
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: Provides a vertical, lateral or temporal range to a 4D point when clearances are provided in the form of: block altitude clearances offsets for deviations due to weather assigned speed ranges .Point Range: Provides a vertical, lateral or temporal range to a 4D point when clearances are provided in the form of:block altitude clearancesoffsets for deviations due to weatherassigned speed ranges

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: TemporalRange
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: Temporal range resulting from assigned speed range.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: Trajectory
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: For FIXM v3.0, this data type only covers the airborne segment. However, future versions of FIXM will cover gate-to-gate operations.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: TrajectoryChange
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: Groups information about features crossed associated with the trajectory point.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: TrajectoryChangePointType
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: Trajectory Change Point - Type: Identifies the type(s) of trajectory change point being described by the associated 4D Point. .Trajectory Change Point - Type: Identifies the type(s) of trajectory change point being described by the associated 4D Point.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: TrajectoryPoint
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: .Trajectory Point: A container for information pertinent to a single point in a trajectory.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: TrajectoryRoutePair
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: Groups and associates a Route and 4D Trajectory.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: AltitudeInTransition
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: .Boundary Crossing Level - Transition/Coordinated: An altitude (flight level) at or above/below which an aircraft will cross the associated boundary point. .Boundary Crossing Level - Transition - Proposed: The proposed altitude (flight level) at or above/below which an aircraft will cross the associated boundary point, as requested by the accepting controller from the transferring controller. .Boundary Crossing Level - Transition: An altitude (flight level) at or above/below which (specified in Boundary Crossing Condition) an aircraft will cross the associated boundary point.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: BoundaryCrossing
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: Abstract Boundary Crossing contains shared data between the BoundaryCrossingProposed and BoundaryCrossingCoordinated classes.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: BoundaryCrossingCondition
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: .Boundary Crossing Condition: Indicator of whether an aircraft will cross an associated boundary crossing point at or above, or at or below the altitude specified by the Boundary Crossing Level - Transition.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: Handoff
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: An action taken to transfer the radar identification of an aircraft from one controller to another controller if the aircraft will enter the receiving controller's airspace and radio communications with the aircraft will be transferred.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: UnitBoundary
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: Represents an Unit boundary that will be traversed En Route. .Unit Boundary: Identifies the unit whose boundary the flight is expected to traverse, based on the planned route of flight and altitude.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: UnitBoundaryIndicator
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: .Unit Boundary Indicator: An indicator of the status of the boundary crossing in the Unit Boundary List as a past crossing, the current or next crossing, or a future crossing.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: AbrogationReasonCode
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: .Abrogation Reason: If the Coordination Status is abrogated, indicating coordination is abolished by authoritative action, the reason the coordination was terminated.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: CoordinationStatus
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: .Coordination Status: The status of Coordination and Transfer of Control between the currently Controlling Air Traffic Service Unit (ATSU) to the downstream to be Controlling ATSU.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: CoordinationStatusCode
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: .Coordination Status: The status of Coordination and Transfer of Control between the currently Controlling Air Traffic Service Unit (ATSU) to the downstream to be Controlling ATSU.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: NonStandardCoordinationReason
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: .Reason for Non-Standard Coordination: In case of non-standard coordination, the reason for non-standard coordination is indicated.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: ReleaseConditions
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: .Release Conditions: When the flight is released from the agreed transfer conditions, contains the Release conditions specified by the transferring ATSUs. The Release conditions indicate the type of manoeuvres the flight is released to perform.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: ClearedFlightInformation
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: Groups cleared information about the fight

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: DirectRouting
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: .Cleared Direct To: Contains the optional starting location from which the direct clearance is granted and the position the aircraft has been cleared directly to.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: EnRoute
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: Groups the en route information about the flight such as the current position, coordination between air traffic units, and boundary crossing throughout the duration of the flight.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: ActualSpeed
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: .Speed - Actual: The actual speed of the aircraft, collected via various methods.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: AircraftPosition
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: Contains the current position and associated data of the aircraft.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: PlannedReportingPosition
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: .Aircraft Planned Reporting Position: Estimated future position, altitude and time of the aircraft transmitted in a non-radar airspace position report.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: PositionReportSource
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: .Current Position Report Source: The source of the current position report information.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: AltitudeQualifier
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: Specifies that the altitude specified in the ClimbToLevelConstraint is not a maximum altitude, and aircraft may climb to a higher level.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: ClimbToLevelConstraint
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: .Change Cruise Climb: The parameters of a cruise climb executed at the associated significant point. It contains the following parameters: 1. the speed to be maintained during cruise climb; 2. either the minimum and maximum levels defining the layer to be occupied during cruise climb, or the level above which cruise climb is planned. .Route-Change Cruise Climb: The parameters of a cruise climb executed at the associated significant point.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: ConstraintOrPreferenceCategory
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: .Constraint Category: Specifies the category (implying a relative importance) of the constraint associated with a point in the route or expanded route.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: LevelConstraint
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: .Route-Change Speed and Altitude: The planned speed and altitude the aircraft will change to either prior to, or after reaching, the associated Significant Point along its Route. .Change Speed and Altitude: The planned speed and altitude that the aircraft will change to upon reaching the associated Significant Point along its Route.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: PositionQualifier
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: Qualifies the position associated with the constraint.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: RouteConstraintOrPreference
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: A constraint that is applicable to a route. Can be any of the several defined constraints.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: SpeedConstraint
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: .Route-Change Speed and Altitude: The planned speed and altitude the aircraft will change to either prior to, or after reaching, the associated Significant Point along its Route. .Change Speed and Altitude: The planned speed and altitude that the aircraft will change to upon reaching the associated Significant Point along its Route.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: TimeConstraint
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: Time Constraint associated with a route point or with other constraint. .Route-Change Speed and Altitude at Time: The planned speed and altitude the aircraft will change to relative to the associated time. .Route-Fix Time - Required: Contains the time at fix and the time at fix constraint condition, which together describe when the aircraft should arrive at a particular fix.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: TimeQualifier
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: Qualifies the time associated with the constraint.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: AbstractRoutePoint
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: An abstract route point containing basic shared data between RoutePoint and ExpandedRoutePoint.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: ClearanceLimitIndicator
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: .Clearance Limit: The point to which an aircraft is granted an air traffic control clearance.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: ElapsedTimeLocation
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: The location associated with estimated elapsed time. It can be a longitude, significant point of flight information region.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: EstimatedElapsedTime
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: .Elapsed Time - Estimated: The estimated amount of time from takeoff to reach a significant point or Flight Information Region (FIR) boundary along the route of flight.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: ExpandedRoute
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: .Expanded Route: The expansion of the route into a set of points which describe the aircraft's expected 2D path from the departure aerodrome to the destination aerodrome.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: ExpandedRoutePoint
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: .Expanded Route Point: A point that is part of the aircraft's expanded route of flight.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: Route
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: Contains information about the Flight Route. The route is comprised of Route Segments, which are comprised of Route Point/Airway pairs. Route also contains an expanded route. .Route: The ICAO route string as depicted from the flight plan.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: RoutePoint
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: Route point along a route of the flight.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: RouteSegment
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: Route Segment contained within the route. Each segment may contain a route point and an airway.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: AtsRoute
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: The coded designator for a published ATS route or route segment.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: UnitSectorAirspace
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: A subdivision of the airspace.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: Altitude
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: Simple altitude type: single measurement above specified reference point.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: VerticalRate
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: .Vertical Rate: An expression of an aircraft's vertical rate of change (climb if positive, descent if negative) expressed as a float [(-3000)-3000] if expressed in ft/min, [(-15)-15] if expressed in m/s.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: GeographicLocation
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: Represents a location by latitude and longitude reference. The "srsName" attribute names the coordinate reference system (CRS) that defines the semantics of the lat/long pair according to the ISO6709 standard. FIXM uses only "urn:ogc:def:crs:EPSG::4326".

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: Longitude
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: Either ddd[EW] or dddmm[EW] format.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: AirspeedMeasure
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: Provides units of measure for airspeeds.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: Angle
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: This is a placeholder for gml:AngleType.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: Groundspeed
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: The Groundspeed type represents any ground speed measurement, in metric. or imperial, as specified by the "uom" attribute.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: GroundspeedMeasure
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: Qualifies the Groundspeed type with metric or imperial units of measure.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: Pressure
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: Describes the atmospheric pressure.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: PressureMeasure
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: Units of measurement for the pressure value.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: Temperature
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: Represents temperature on a specific scale

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: TemperatureMeasure
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: Provides units of measure for Temperature.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: TrueAirspeedOrMach
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: The Airspeed type represents any airspeed measurement, in metric. imperial, or Mach units, as specified by the "uom" attribute.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: UnitOfMeasure
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: Abstract Supertype for all units of measure. Takes the place of gml:UnitOfMeasureType.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: WindDirection
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: Indicates the direction of the wind which is a specialization of the angle.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: Windspeed
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: Indicates the Speed of wind.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: WindSpeedMeasure
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: Indicates the units of measure for Wind Speed.

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: Duration
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: Extent of time without reference to start or stop times. This is a placeholder for gml:DurationType

rdfs:Class.rdfs:label: Time
rdfs:Class.rdfs:comment: A Time instant placeholder for gml:TimePositionType, in its XML dataTime variation.
